In a speech at the National Association of Manufacturers, President Trump discussed the federal mobilization efforts to assist Puerto Rico after the devastating hurricanes, stating that the government will work with Puerto Rico to determine how the massive rebuilding effort will be funded and organized. He also mentioned the disaster recovery efforts in the Virgin Islands. The President then focused on his vision for America's economic revival, highlighting the importance of "Made in the USA" and announcing his administration's plan for tax reform. The four core principles of the plan include cutting taxes for individuals and families, simplifying the tax code, reducing the business tax rate, and encouraging American companies to bring back trillions of dollars in wealth parked overseas. President Trump emphasized the need to create jobs, increase wages, and strengthen American industry. He concluded by expressing his belief in the American Dream and his commitment to building a future of opportunity and prosperity for all citizens.